1
00:00:09,967 --> 00:00:12,000
<i>Hazel, do you really think
I don't see what you're doing?</i>

2
00:00:12,133 --> 00:00:14,600
<i>You're using me so you can
get your husband back.</i>

3
00:00:14,733 --> 00:00:16,700
<i>I'm sorry,
but I'm not doing that.</i>

4
00:00:16,833 --> 00:00:18,867
<i> Noah, thanks for teaching me.</i>

5
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:20,600
<i> Not everything came from me.</i>

6
00:00:20,733 --> 00:00:22,700
<i>You have your own
very efficient way, too.</i>

7
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:25,700
<i>Dad, thank you for everything
you and mom do</i>

8
00:00:25,833 --> 00:00:27,467
<i>so I won't be too tense
for the hearing.</i>

9
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:31,200
<i>Just remember that you
only need to tell the truth.</i>

10
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:32,600
<i>That you didn't do
anything wrong.</i>

11
00:00:32,733 --> 00:00:34,033
<i> If you can do that,</i>

12
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:37,200
<i>Jessica's death
will finally be given justice.</i>

13
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:38,967
<i> On the day of the accident,</i>

14
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:42,600
<i>you didn't actually see Coleen
push Jessica, right?</i>

15
00:00:42,733 --> 00:00:44,400
<i> That's right. I didn't see it.</i>

16
00:00:44,533 --> 00:00:46,033
<i> Have you personally witnessed</i>

17
00:00:46,167 --> 00:00:48,067
<i>Coleen threatening
to kill Jessica?</i>

18
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:49,333
<i> No.</i>

19
00:00:49,467 --> 00:00:52,200
<i>It's also possible that
it really was just an accident.</i>

20
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:53,500
<i> Objection, Your Honor!</i>

21
00:00:53,633 --> 00:00:55,267
<i> Speculative!</i>

22
00:01:00,733 --> 00:01:02,033
Your Honor, I'm only...

23
00:01:02,167 --> 00:01:03,700
trying to establish

24
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:05,900
that Mrs. Cruz knows
nothing about...

25
00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:07,533
- Coleen's true intentions.
- Objection!

26
00:01:07,700 --> 00:01:08,933
Argumentative!

27
00:01:10,567 --> 00:01:11,800
Overruled.

28
00:01:11,933 --> 00:01:13,933
The witness may answer.

29
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:16,467
Impossible.

30
00:01:16,600 --> 00:01:19,533
It's impossible that
Jessica's death was an accident.

31
00:01:20,300 --> 00:01:23,033
I've caught her hurting
Jessica so many times!

32
00:01:23,167 --> 00:01:26,400
Even before Jessica died,
she told me that herself.

33
00:01:26,533 --> 00:01:28,533
<i> So admit it, Coleen.</i>

34
00:01:28,667 --> 00:01:30,633
You hurt Jessica, didn't you?

35
00:01:30,767 --> 00:01:32,333
I didn't mean to.

36
00:01:32,467 --> 00:01:34,400
You didn't mean to?
You were jealous of her!

37
00:01:34,533 --> 00:01:36,167
- Order! Counsel!
- That's why you did it!

38
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:37,900
<i>- Counsel!
- Just admit it, Coleen!</i>

39
00:01:38,033 --> 00:01:40,933
<i> Restrain your clients!</i>

40
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:43,167
Mrs. Cruz, that's enough.

41
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:58,067
Your Honor,

42
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:00,700
that woman is violent.

43
00:02:00,833 --> 00:02:02,767
She hurts people.

44
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:06,500
She's capable of killing.
I believe she killed Jessica.

45
00:02:06,633 --> 00:02:08,533
She killed my daughter!

46
00:02:08,667 --> 00:02:10,267
Enough, Hazel!

47
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,833
Stop blaming my daughter.

48
00:02:12,967 --> 00:02:16,733
- Fight fair.
- Order! Order in the court!

49
00:02:33,033 --> 00:02:34,233
Sweetheart,

50
00:02:34,367 --> 00:02:36,333
maybe you should rest for now?

51
00:02:36,467 --> 00:02:38,600
We just need to talk
to the attorney.

52
00:02:40,167 --> 00:02:41,267
Thank you, Andrea.

53
00:02:42,233 --> 00:02:44,333
But, Mom, I want to hear it.

54
00:02:45,733 --> 00:02:47,133
Sweetie,

55
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:48,967
we actually didn't want you to.

56
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:52,433
We were trying to keep you
from losing hope.

57
00:02:53,300 --> 00:02:54,567
Dad, I can do this.

58
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:57,167
I'll manage.

59
00:03:02,267 --> 00:03:03,100
Attorney,

60
00:03:05,067 --> 00:03:07,467
will what happened
in the hearing...

61
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:09,600
help the case?

62
00:03:11,433 --> 00:03:14,767
I can't say it helped much.

63
00:03:16,133 --> 00:03:19,800
The prosecution tried
to establish a motive.

64
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:22,333
What Hazel said,

65
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:25,367
your jealousy, your supposed
violent tendencies,

66
00:03:26,633 --> 00:03:29,533
and what she claims she
witnessed, you hurting Jessica.

67
00:03:29,667 --> 00:03:31,267
She's lying!

68
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,967
She added so much
that never happened!

69
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:37,233
Andrea, it's true.
I did hurt Jessica.

70
00:03:37,367 --> 00:03:40,900
Also, we can't discount
the driver's testimony.

71
00:03:41,033 --> 00:03:42,300
Timo Malabanan.

72
00:03:43,333 --> 00:03:45,033
I tried to prove that...

73
00:03:45,167 --> 00:03:47,533
what he saw was wrong.

74
00:03:47,667 --> 00:03:49,367
That you didn't push Jessica.

75
00:03:50,267 --> 00:03:51,933
But in the end, it's still
the court that will decide.

76
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,567
Attorney,

77
00:03:55,267 --> 00:03:56,567
what else can we do?

78
00:03:57,733 --> 00:04:00,967
If only someone had witnessed
the accident.

79
00:04:02,067 --> 00:04:02,933
Attorney,

80
00:04:03,467 --> 00:04:06,300
there were a few people
in that area at the time.

81
00:04:07,467 --> 00:04:09,067
Yes, I already talked to them.

82
00:04:09,933 --> 00:04:11,600
According to them...

83
00:04:11,733 --> 00:04:13,533
they only turned
their heads when...

84
00:04:14,367 --> 00:04:15,900
they heard the accident.

85
00:04:16,033 --> 00:04:18,433
But none of them actually saw
what really happened.

86
00:04:21,367 --> 00:04:22,400
We can look around.

87
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,400
Maybe someone else saw it.

88
00:04:26,233 --> 00:04:27,300
And this time,

89
00:04:28,867 --> 00:04:30,967
a witness might come forward.

90
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:32,600
Attorney,

91
00:04:33,533 --> 00:04:35,200
just tell us how we can help.

92
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:36,567
We're willing.

93
00:04:36,700 --> 00:04:37,600
Well...

94
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,767
Right now,

95
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:41,967
what we really need to do
is to...

96
00:04:42,567 --> 00:04:44,100
get you ready, Coleen.

97
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:48,000
The defense will open
the next hearing.

98
00:04:48,633 --> 00:04:50,367
That's your chance
to tell the truth.

99
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,333
But you still need
to prepare, because...

100
00:04:55,267 --> 00:04:56,533
the prosecution...

101
00:04:57,733 --> 00:05:00,633
will twist your words
during cross-examination.

102
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:13,567
The defense calls
its first witness to the stand,

103
00:05:13,967 --> 00:05:15,267
Coleen Cruz.

104
00:05:30,833 --> 00:05:32,100
Swear in the witness.

105
00:05:34,733 --> 00:05:36,367
<i> Please raise your right hand.</i>

106
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:43,967
Do you swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth,

107
00:05:44,100 --> 00:05:45,833
and nothing but the truth
in this court?

108
00:05:46,667 --> 00:05:47,667
Yes, I do.

109
00:05:48,467 --> 00:05:49,800
<i> You may now take your seat.</i>

110
00:05:54,333 --> 00:05:57,933
<i>Your Honor, we present the
testimony of the witness</i>

111
00:05:58,067 --> 00:06:00,033
to prove that she did not
commit the crime alleged

112
00:06:00,167 --> 00:06:01,767
in the information.

113
00:06:01,900 --> 00:06:03,567
Comment from the prosecution?

114
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:06,533
Subject to cross, Your Honor.

115
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:08,533
Your Honor, may we proceed?

116
00:06:08,700 --> 00:06:10,000
Proceed.

117
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:15,067
Miss Cruz,

118
00:06:17,133 --> 00:06:21,100
can you tell this court

119
00:06:21,233 --> 00:06:25,900
what happened moments
before the accident?

120
00:06:26,033 --> 00:06:30,533
We met Jessica that day
at the hospital.

121
00:06:30,667 --> 00:06:34,133
My brother Jeffrey brought
our father, Manuel Cruz,

122
00:06:34,267 --> 00:06:35,900
back to the hospital.

123
00:06:36,033 --> 00:06:40,800
Hazel took him out even though
he wasn't well yet.

124
00:06:40,967 --> 00:06:43,000
We argued a bit.

125
00:06:43,133 --> 00:06:45,667
<i>You just let your mother
sneak dad out!</i>

126
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,533
<i> We were all worried!</i>

127
00:06:47,667 --> 00:06:50,633
<i> I tried to stop mom.</i>

128
00:06:50,767 --> 00:06:54,200
I just wanted us to make peace.

129
00:06:54,333 --> 00:07:01,000
But when her mother, Hazel,
saw us,

130
00:07:01,133 --> 00:07:04,767
she thought
I was hurting Jessica.

131
00:07:04,900 --> 00:07:06,800
So she attacked me.

132
00:07:06,933 --> 00:07:08,933
Don't believe that woman!

133
00:07:09,067 --> 00:07:11,100
She's lying again!

134
00:07:11,233 --> 00:07:13,633
What she's saying isn't true!
You liar!

135
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,167
- Your Honor.
- Why can't you say the truth?

136
00:07:15,300 --> 00:07:16,667
Don't believe her!

137
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:19,700
Your Honor,
Mrs. Hazel Cruz's outburst

138
00:07:19,833 --> 00:07:21,067
is disrupting the proceedings.

139
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:23,900
We would like to move to
cite her in contempt of court.

140
00:07:24,567 --> 00:07:26,167
Mrs. Cruz,

141
00:07:26,300 --> 00:07:30,533
if you speak out of line again
and disrupt these proceedings,

142
00:07:30,667 --> 00:07:33,067
<i>I will cite you
for direct contempt.</i>

143
00:07:34,933 --> 00:07:36,200
Sorry, Miss Cruz.

144
00:07:36,333 --> 00:07:38,033
You may continue.

145
00:07:38,167 --> 00:07:41,133
Jessica tried
to hold her mom back,

146
00:07:42,333 --> 00:07:45,300
but she kept hurting me.

147
00:07:47,433 --> 00:07:52,433
Then my siblings arrived
to help us.

148
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:53,500
<i> But...</i>

149
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:57,300
but Jessica got tired
of stopping her mom,

150
00:07:57,433 --> 00:07:59,400
so she walked out.

151
00:08:02,933 --> 00:08:04,300
<i> All you do is fight!</i>

152
00:08:04,433 --> 00:08:06,233
<i> All you bring is trouble!</i>

153
00:08:08,467 --> 00:08:11,433
What happened after that?

154
00:08:11,567 --> 00:08:14,533
I followed her
because I wanted us to talk.

155
00:08:16,433 --> 00:08:19,367
But she was angry.
She didn't want to talk.

156
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:23,667
I tried to stop her
from leaving,

157
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:27,533
but she broke free from me.

158
00:08:27,667 --> 00:08:28,667
<i> Jessica!</i>

159
00:08:29,567 --> 00:08:31,333
<i> Jessica!</i>

160
00:08:35,767 --> 00:08:37,000
Miss Cruz,

161
00:08:37,133 --> 00:08:39,033
what reason would you have to...

162
00:08:39,167 --> 00:08:41,233
hurt the victim?

163
00:08:42,567 --> 00:08:44,467
None.

164
00:08:45,433 --> 00:08:47,333
I love Jessica.

165
00:08:48,233 --> 00:08:51,133
I love my sister very much.

166
00:09:06,633 --> 00:09:08,767
You said earlier that...

167
00:09:10,867 --> 00:09:14,067
you tried to stop her
from leaving.

168
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,900
So that means...

169
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:20,100
you held her, correct?

170
00:09:21,067 --> 00:09:21,967
Yes.

171
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:26,467
Your hand made contact with her,
correct?

172
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:28,000
Yes.

173
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:30,800
- So you pushed her?
- Objection, Your Honor.

174
00:09:30,933 --> 00:09:31,867
Misleading.

175
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:34,133
<i> Sustained.</i>

176
00:09:34,267 --> 00:09:36,267
Rephrase your question, Counsel.

177
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:37,500
Yes, Your Honor.

178
00:09:38,633 --> 00:09:41,133
According to the victim's
mother,

179
00:09:42,300 --> 00:09:45,067
when she saw her daughter
bleeding

180
00:09:45,933 --> 00:09:47,267
and lying...

181
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:50,167
on the road,

182
00:09:50,667 --> 00:09:52,833
the first thing you said was

183
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:55,333
"I didn't mean to."
Is that correct?

184
00:09:55,467 --> 00:09:56,633
No.

185
00:09:57,433 --> 00:09:59,767
<i>- What did you do?
- Nothing!</i>

186
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:02,100
<i> Nothing! I didn't do anything!</i>

187
00:10:02,267 --> 00:10:03,433
<i> Jessica!</i>

188
00:10:03,567 --> 00:10:05,900
You said
"I didn't mean to"

189
00:10:06,033 --> 00:10:09,200
before anyone even accused you
of anything.

190
00:10:09,867 --> 00:10:12,733
So why did it seem like
you already knew...

191
00:10:12,867 --> 00:10:14,433
people would blame you?

192
00:10:14,933 --> 00:10:16,267
Objection, Your Honor.

193
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:17,500
Argumentative.

194
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:19,300
Overruled.

195
00:10:20,367 --> 00:10:22,733
I never said
"I didn't mean to,"

196
00:10:22,867 --> 00:10:25,367
because I never pushed Jessica.

197
00:10:31,333 --> 00:10:32,333
So...

198
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:36,900
how do you feel
about the victim's death?

199
00:10:38,067 --> 00:10:40,933
I'm sad because
I couldn't save her.

200
00:10:41,767 --> 00:10:43,400
I wish I had pulled her back.

201
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:48,000
So you feel responsible
for her death?

202
00:10:49,033 --> 00:10:51,567
No. Not like that.

203
00:10:52,367 --> 00:10:54,633
I'm sad because my sister died.

204
00:10:54,767 --> 00:10:56,567
She shouldn't have died.

205
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:59,133
She died because you pushed her!

206
00:10:59,267 --> 00:11:01,033
You let my daughter
get run over!

207
00:11:01,167 --> 00:11:02,267
- You let her die!
- Order!

208
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:03,233
- That's what happened!
- Order in the court!

209
00:11:03,367 --> 00:11:04,600
Stop lying, Coleen!

210
00:11:04,733 --> 00:11:06,867
One more word from your client

211
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,500
and I will cite her in contempt,
Counsel!

212
00:11:13,533 --> 00:11:14,867
My apologies, Your Honor.

213
00:11:29,467 --> 00:11:31,200
I feel so sorry for my daughter.

214
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:33,967
What she's going through
is so heavy.

215
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,900
I just hope
this leads somewhere.

216
00:11:37,867 --> 00:11:40,100
I hope we win this, Attorney.

217
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:45,600
Honestly, it's hard
to say right now,

218
00:11:45,767 --> 00:11:48,267
especially after
what happened earlier.

219
00:11:49,533 --> 00:11:52,267
Coleen was confused
and vulnerable.

220
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:55,367
The court might think...

221
00:11:57,467 --> 00:12:00,600
she feels guilty
about Jessica's death.

222
00:12:03,733 --> 00:12:05,867
What can we do, Attorney?

223
00:12:07,100 --> 00:12:08,367
Well...

224
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:10,567
Jeffrey and Noah
are already helping

225
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:13,433
look for a possible witness
to the accident,

226
00:12:13,567 --> 00:12:17,067
but we still don't have anyone.

227
00:12:17,967 --> 00:12:19,800
<i> The only one we can rely on...</i>

228
00:12:21,567 --> 00:12:23,167
is the driver...

229
00:12:23,300 --> 00:12:25,333
<i> Timo Malabanan.</i>

230
00:12:25,467 --> 00:12:27,767
We need to prove that...

231
00:12:28,467 --> 00:12:30,133
he's not telling the truth.

232
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:41,533
Hurry up, friend.

233
00:12:41,667 --> 00:12:43,567
Our friends are waiting!

234
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:44,967
Where is it again?

235
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:46,967
The new place
that just opened in BGC.

236
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:48,367
- Oh?
- They say the crowd's great.

237
00:12:48,533 --> 00:12:51,100
- Come on, let's go!
- I can't wait to celebrate

238
00:12:51,233 --> 00:12:52,467
my victory.

239
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,433
Because I'm sure that Coleen
is going straight to city jail.

240
00:13:03,067 --> 00:13:04,533
What are you doing here?

241
00:13:06,267 --> 00:13:07,333
How did you get in?

242
00:13:08,733 --> 00:13:09,933
The gate was open.

243
00:13:12,100 --> 00:13:13,933
You're trespassing.

244
00:13:14,467 --> 00:13:15,800
I could easily have you charged.

245
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:22,200
I came here
to talk peacefully, Hazel.

246
00:13:23,433 --> 00:13:24,433
Wow.

247
00:13:25,367 --> 00:13:26,567
Acting all nice now?

248
00:13:27,967 --> 00:13:29,300
Where'd your fangs go?

249
00:13:30,300 --> 00:13:32,567
Anyway, whatever your reason
for coming here,

250
00:13:32,700 --> 00:13:35,100
I don't care
and I don't have time.

251
00:13:35,233 --> 00:13:36,800
I'm going to a victory party.

252
00:13:38,433 --> 00:13:42,333
To celebrate what you're doing
to my daughter?

253
00:13:43,133 --> 00:13:44,300
You're pinning it on her.

254
00:13:45,333 --> 00:13:47,900
You're forcing a story
that isn't even true.

255
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:50,567
Are you stupid?

256
00:13:51,533 --> 00:13:55,567
Weren't you there
when Timo Malabanan testified?

257
00:13:55,733 --> 00:13:59,400
He clearly saw Coleen
push Jessica.

258
00:14:01,167 --> 00:14:02,500
I talked to Timo.

259
00:14:03,867 --> 00:14:06,167
I can feel he's lying.

260
00:14:07,033 --> 00:14:11,133
<i>Why would you say Coleen
pushed Jessica?</i>

261
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:12,833
<i>Because that's
what really happened.</i>

262
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:16,133
What exactly are you
trying to say?

263
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:20,000
I did something
to Timo to make him lie?

264
00:14:21,967 --> 00:14:23,200
You said it, not me.

265
00:14:26,067 --> 00:14:28,267
So that's how powerful
you think I am?

266
00:14:29,133 --> 00:14:32,867
I can buy off a driver
and promise him anything?

267
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:35,133
Then prove it.

268
00:14:36,233 --> 00:14:37,367
Bring it to court.

269
00:14:38,100 --> 00:14:40,767
Let's see which one of us
ends up humiliated.

270
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:42,933
Easy for you to say...

271
00:14:44,633 --> 00:14:47,533
because you know
it's hard to prove.

272
00:14:48,367 --> 00:14:50,700
Your lawyer's all style
and no substance.

273
00:14:51,700 --> 00:14:52,533
But, fine.

274
00:14:53,633 --> 00:14:56,200
Let's say, hypothetically...

275
00:14:58,267 --> 00:15:01,367
Do you really think
I'd drop the case?

276
00:15:02,167 --> 00:15:05,900
Felma, I lost my daughter.

277
00:15:07,267 --> 00:15:09,667
If it happened to you,
wouldn't you?

278
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:13,167
You'll do everything to give her
justice for what happended.

279
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:14,433
You're right.

280
00:15:15,433 --> 00:15:17,000
I would do everything.

281
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:19,433
That's exactly why I'm here.

282
00:15:20,367 --> 00:15:21,900
Because I want to know
the truth.

283
00:15:22,967 --> 00:15:26,567
You're here because you want me
to drop the case?

284
00:15:33,067 --> 00:15:34,800
Can you do that?

285
00:15:40,167 --> 00:15:42,533
How far are you willing to go
for Coleen?

286
00:15:44,067 --> 00:15:45,433
Can you...

287
00:15:48,033 --> 00:15:49,100
kneel?

288
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:53,567
Kiss my feet?

289
00:15:54,167 --> 00:15:56,267
- Friend.
- Let her.

290
00:15:57,200 --> 00:16:00,800
Let's see how much
she really loves Coleen.

291
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:11,300
Hazel!

292
00:16:15,067 --> 00:16:16,467
Hazel...

293
00:16:21,667 --> 00:16:22,867
You animal!

294
00:16:24,133 --> 00:16:25,533
Monster! How dare you!

295
00:16:25,667 --> 00:16:27,933
- Enough!
- You're in my house!

296
00:16:28,067 --> 00:16:29,900
Enough! This could get worse!

297
00:16:30,033 --> 00:16:31,533
Just leave, Felma!

298
00:16:31,667 --> 00:16:34,033
I will never kneel to you,
Hazel.

299
00:16:34,167 --> 00:16:35,667
I kneel only before God!

300
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:36,767
Oh, really?

301
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:38,433
Then why are you here
in our house?

302
00:16:38,567 --> 00:16:40,467
- Friend, that's enough.
- Because I was hoping

303
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:44,900
that somehow you'd grow a heart,
you're a mother, too!

304
00:16:45,067 --> 00:16:46,767
Yes, I'm a mother.

305
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:49,100
A mother who lost her child
because of your daughter!

306
00:16:49,233 --> 00:16:49,967
No!

307
00:16:51,067 --> 00:16:54,000
A mother who lost her child
because of an accident

308
00:16:54,133 --> 00:16:56,033
that you keep twisting into a
crime my daughter didn't commit!

309
00:16:56,167 --> 00:16:57,267
Then keep denying!

310
00:16:57,400 --> 00:17:00,000
Even after Timo's testimony
slapped you in the face!

311
00:17:00,133 --> 00:17:02,533
A testimony that was fabricated.

312
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:05,900
Because you paid him to lie!
You ordered him.

313
00:17:06,033 --> 00:17:08,667
You're the one making up
stories, Felma!

314
00:17:08,900 --> 00:17:09,967
Oh, really, Hazel?

315
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:17,600
Fine.

316
00:17:17,733 --> 00:17:18,733
Go on, say it.

317
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:25,600
Swear on your daughter
that you didn't pay Timo

318
00:17:25,733 --> 00:17:29,500
to make up a story,
to frame my child!

319
00:17:34,700 --> 00:17:35,967
So it's true.

320
00:17:38,633 --> 00:17:40,467
So it's true.

321
00:17:42,133 --> 00:17:43,300
What are you saying?

322
00:17:44,267 --> 00:17:46,700
I didn't say anything
and I have nothing to admit!

323
00:17:46,833 --> 00:17:47,933
Friend...

324
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:52,500
But your silence?
It's loud enough.

325
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:58,000
It's screaming the truth
that you paid Timo,

326
00:17:58,133 --> 00:18:00,833
and you can't even deny it
in front of your own daughter!

327
00:18:01,067 --> 00:18:02,533
Get out of my house...

328
00:18:03,233 --> 00:18:05,333
before I file charges
for assault and trespassing!

329
00:18:05,467 --> 00:18:07,167
You can rot in jail
with your daughter!

330
00:18:07,300 --> 00:18:09,367
- Give me that!
- Get out, Felma!

331
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:11,400
- Leave! Get out!
- Get out!

332
00:18:11,533 --> 00:18:15,300
I won't stop until
the truth comes out.

333
00:18:15,433 --> 00:18:19,267
You, not Coleen,
will end up in jail!

334
00:18:27,833 --> 00:18:29,567
Mom, why did you even go there?

335
00:18:30,967 --> 00:18:34,267
When dad and I go to Hazel,
you get angry.

336
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:37,967
And now you went alone?
You're so brave.

337
00:18:38,100 --> 00:18:39,167
That's right, Mom.

338
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:42,900
Good thing that demon
didn't hurt you.

339
00:18:44,933 --> 00:18:46,067
No.

340
00:18:47,700 --> 00:18:49,000
I won't let that happen.

341
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:50,800
Good.

342
00:18:51,567 --> 00:18:52,867
So what now, Mom? Did you get
anything from her?

343
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,233
Nothing, right?

344
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:55,633
I did.

345
00:18:57,600 --> 00:18:58,500
Even if...

346
00:18:59,767 --> 00:19:03,633
she didn't say it outright,
I caught her.

347
00:19:04,533 --> 00:19:05,233
Mom...

348
00:19:06,667 --> 00:19:11,067
It doesn't mean just because
Hazel didn't answer you,

349
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:12,467
she admitted anything.

350
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:16,500
Silence doesn't always mean yes.

351
00:19:16,633 --> 00:19:19,200
But a mother's instinct is real.

352
00:19:19,333 --> 00:19:20,467
I'm a mother.

353
00:19:21,733 --> 00:19:23,467
And I saw in another
mother's eyes....

354
00:19:24,900 --> 00:19:26,133
the truth.

355
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:28,133
You, my children...

356
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,200
I can look you in the eye...

357
00:19:32,267 --> 00:19:36,233
and answer anything you ask me.

358
00:19:37,833 --> 00:19:38,967
But Hazel?

359
00:19:40,567 --> 00:19:42,233
Even looking at the picture
of her own daughter...

360
00:19:43,267 --> 00:19:46,233
she couldn't even look
and say...

361
00:19:47,100 --> 00:19:49,433
that she didn't pay Timo.

362
00:19:50,300 --> 00:19:51,767
I'll go back to see Timo.

363
00:19:52,100 --> 00:19:54,100
What? Why, Mom?

364
00:19:54,767 --> 00:19:55,967
You think he'll confess?

365
00:19:56,733 --> 00:19:59,467
Mom, if Hazel really paid him,

366
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:02,067
he's even less likely
to take it back.

367
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:06,967
What we need to do
is prove that he's a liar.

368
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:11,567
When it's time for Coleen's
defense in court.

369
00:20:12,933 --> 00:20:14,100
Mom, I'm sorry, okay?

370
00:20:14,633 --> 00:20:15,967
But if I have to...

371
00:20:17,567 --> 00:20:19,000
I'll destroy Jessica's image.

372
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:23,833
So Coleen won't look bad
in the eyes of the judge.

373
00:20:35,367 --> 00:20:37,167
Don't ever do that, kids.

374
00:20:39,133 --> 00:20:43,333
I don't want any of you to lie.

375
00:20:45,533 --> 00:20:49,700
And I don't want Jessica's
memory to be stained.

376
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:51,500
Then what do we do, Mom?

377
00:20:52,667 --> 00:20:54,033
I don't know yet.

378
00:20:56,433 --> 00:21:01,467
But I don't want us
lying in court.

379
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:03,433
We will only tell the truth.

380
00:21:05,667 --> 00:21:08,033
No one in this family will lie.

381
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:32,200
Felma, are you okay?

382
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:34,600
Yes, yes.

383
00:21:36,133 --> 00:21:38,033
My head just suddenly
started hurting.

384
00:21:39,233 --> 00:21:42,500
Manuel, how are we going
to fight this?

385
00:21:43,567 --> 00:21:45,567
Felma, I honestly
don't know anymore.

386
00:21:47,233 --> 00:21:48,733
You know what I'm thinking?

387
00:21:49,233 --> 00:21:51,700
Maybe we should do
what Jeffrey suggested.

388
00:21:52,733 --> 00:21:55,467
What is?
Destroy Jessica's image?

389
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:58,133
- Manuel, no.
- No, not Jessica.

390
00:21:58,267 --> 00:21:59,500
Timo.

391
00:21:59,633 --> 00:22:01,333
We destroy his credibility.

392
00:22:01,467 --> 00:22:05,667
We'll find someone
we can ask to...

393
00:22:05,967 --> 00:22:06,567
What?

394
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:14,000
You'll recruit someone
to make up a story

395
00:22:14,133 --> 00:22:18,867
so we can ruin
the prosecution's witness?

396
00:22:19,767 --> 00:22:23,700
Atty. Yeban said, everyone
he talked to about Timo

397
00:22:23,833 --> 00:22:25,233
had nothing
but good things to say.

398
00:22:26,733 --> 00:22:28,567
But I don't believe he's clean.

399
00:22:29,167 --> 00:22:31,500
So I hired
a private investigator...

400
00:22:32,700 --> 00:22:34,533
to dig up the dirt on his life.

401
00:22:35,333 --> 00:22:37,667
If we want to ruin
his credibility,

402
00:22:37,800 --> 00:22:40,100
we need evidence.

403
00:22:47,233 --> 00:22:50,333
The defense has painted
that your daughter

404
00:22:50,500 --> 00:22:53,200
is kind and incapable of harm.

405
00:22:53,333 --> 00:22:55,067
But let's address the issue.

406
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:58,367
Didn't Jessica and Coleen
have multiple arguments

407
00:22:58,500 --> 00:22:59,900
before the incident happened?

408
00:23:00,033 --> 00:23:01,233
That's true.

409
00:23:01,367 --> 00:23:04,333
They had misunderstandings.

410
00:23:04,467 --> 00:23:05,633
Hurt feelings.

411
00:23:06,700 --> 00:23:07,533
Jealousy.

412
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:09,367
So there was jealousy?

413
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:18,033
Mrs. Cruz, you said Jessica
feared for her life.

414
00:23:18,467 --> 00:23:23,433
Did she tell you it was because
Coleen threatened her?

415
00:23:23,833 --> 00:23:24,900
Yes.

416
00:23:25,033 --> 00:23:27,100
Do you have any evidence?

417
00:23:27,233 --> 00:23:32,000
Perhaps a recording or witness
that can confirm it?
